# Mermaid Diagrams

When creating or explaining architecture, flow, sequence, or system diagrams, **always use Mermaid** syntax.

- Use Mermaid code blocks in markdown: ` ```mermaid ` … ` ``` `
- Prefer Mermaid over ASCII art, ASCII boxes, or plain text diagrams
- Supported chart types: flowchart, sequenceDiagram, classDiagram, stateDiagram, erDiagram, etc.

## Example

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph Brain
        A[echo_prism_agent]
    end
    subgraph Modality
        B[LiveKit]
        C[Browser]
    end
    B --> A
    C --> A
```
